RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 5F Turf CR: 77. Maiden Special Weight Purse 27000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. JACKSON ACTION raced in the middle of the pack on the outside early, came around the turn in the three path, began a bid in upper stretch and gained ground late. HARLEEZY raced off the pace up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and improved position in late stretch. POSITIVE PETEY chased the leaders through the opening quarter of a mile, saved ground around the turn and was outkicked in the lane. VICTORYFORTHEPOSSE dueled on the outside up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and weakened in the stretch. PRIDE OF ARGYLE broke slowly, trailed the field up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and made no bid. COWBOY JACK raced in the middle of the pack on the inside through the opening stages, continued around the turn in the two path and faded in the lane. PALACE ATTAINED raced in the middle of the pack early, was taken up while racing in the two path around the turn, pulled up in upper stretch and was vanned off after walking onto the van.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 89. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE FEBRUARY 9 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Races With Winning Earnings Of $4,500 Or Less Not Considered Or Claiming Ra ces For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility). Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $6,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EISENSTAEDT saved ground around the first turn, opened up on the field racing up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far bend, drew off in upper stretch and was geared down at the wire. LAST MARTINI raced off the pace on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, navigated the second turn from the four path and improved position in the lane but was no match for the winner. MISHKO raced in the two path around the first turn, stalked the pace setter up the backstretch, came around the far bend in the three path and chased on to the finish. RELEASE THE BEAST saved ground early, settled in the middle of the pack for the run up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the far turn and kept on in the stretch. FEEDING FRENZY raced in the four path around the first turn, trailed the field between horses up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the two path and never threatened. CHEST CANDY was in tight quarters at the break, trailed the field from the three path around the first bend, raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, began a bid from the rail coming around the far bend and flattened out in the lane. PUSH THROUGH raced in the three path around the first turn, chased the leader up the backstretch, came around the second turn in the two path and tired in the stretch.

FOXY ELAINE led the way on the inside up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the bend, kicked clear in upper stretch and was caught late. RUN WITH PRIDE tracked the pace setter on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, navigated the bend from the three path and was outkicked. SASSY MAMA raced in the middle of the pack through the opening stages, came around the turn in the two path and showed no kick. TWAS was blocked leaving the gate, trailed the field up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the two path and was empty from there. ROCKINMYFEATHERBOA pressed the pace between horses up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and tired in the stretch.
